<br>
People get mad; people say things that they don't mean. That happens when you put 200 pounds of shit in a 50 pound sack. We can thank poor game design for it. I'm sure that our issue in Kael was a prime example of that.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying hold one act against someone and guildremove them. My post was directed at habitual offenders. I'm talking about people that consistantly lose their cool in guildchat/ooc/shout/whatever. I'm talking about people that constantly come to this board and make asses of themselves. The only one-time acts that I think should get someone removed is theft. Ninjalooting, scamming someone, something along that line. What would happen if you alienated every friend and loved one that ever said or did anything that made you angry? You'd be alone.<br>
<br>
I like about 90% of the members of Eternal Wrath. It's that other 10% of you that leave a sour taste in my mouth. You know who you are. The funny part is, most of the people that made a scene in ooc/shout in Kael that night were already part of the 10%. It's sad that 10% of you can all but completely destroy my respect for your guild. I don't know if my opinion is right or wrong. But, it's how I feel, so I'm sticking to it.<br>
<br>
Just the same, Gandien's act may have destroyed your opinion of Casus Belli. You are entitled to hate him all you like. That's the difference between the general public and family. You can completely hate any average Joe for a single act of dumbness. Will you completely hate a family member for a similar act? Gandien is family in this game; I support and defend him to the death.<br>
